Also, the model is always saying Opus in ../threadminer the logger on lines 88-89. The WithModelName(*discoveryModel) means the logger always displays "opus" regardless of which agent is
  running. The logger is shared across all agents since they all use the same client. So the logs say "opus" even when the extraction call is actually
   using haiku.

  The model is being set correctly per-call via claude.WithModel(c.model) in each agent. The log is just misleading. (line numbers might be wrong)

make sure the cost and context window calculations are referencing the right models too. Opus and Haiku should have different context legnths and costs associated so if that shared model name was being used it could be throwing those off too

I want to add an option so you can just look at the meta info call and supress logs if you want. Basically.

[assistant] [rank | haiku | ~12 in + ~0 out / 200.0K (0.0%) | 14.5m]
let's setup threadminer to use the new supress log content option (but show cost and model info)
